Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi will visit Khutlo Tharo Secondary School in Sebokeng in the Vaal to assess the damage caused by a fire on Wednesday morning. The school’s administration block caught fire early on Wednesday morning causing extensive damage. Investigations are under way to determine the cause of the fire. Spokesperson Steve Mabona says Lesufi wants to ensure that the school does go ahead with the school calendar. He says: ‘Lesufi will visit Khutlo Tharo Secondary in Sebokeng following the torching of the school in the early hours of this morning to assess the damage and pave the way forward on school processes.” 